{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/400","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/400/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/400/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/400/events","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan/rich/issues/400","id":726989855,"node_id":"MDU6SXNzdWU3MjY5ODk4NTU=","number":400,"title":"[BUG] Inline markdown formatting for Japanese (probably other languages too)","user":{"login":"1dancook","id":12954427,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyOTU0NDI3","avatar_url":"https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/12954427?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/1dancook","html_url":"https://github.com/1dancook","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1dancook/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1dancook/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1dancook/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1dancook/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1dancook/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1dancook/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1dancook/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1dancook/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1dancook/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":2200581776,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwyMjAwNTgxNzc2","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/labels/Needs%20triage","name":"Needs triage","color":"bfdadc","default":false,"description":""}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":2,"created_at":"2020-10-22T02:22:59Z","updated_at":"2020-10-22T11:44:47Z","closed_at":"2020-10-22T11:44:47Z","author_association":"NONE","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"**Describe the bug**\r\nUsing markdown inline formatting doesn't always work as expected for Japanese.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\n\r\n1. This is not an exhaustive list of cases, but put the following text in a file: test.md\r\n\r\n```\r\n1. **今日**は木曜日です。  \r\n2. **(きょう)**は木曜日です。  \r\n3. **（きょう）**は木曜日です。  \r\n4. **＜きょう＞**は木曜日です。  \r\n5. **きょう」**は木曜日です。  \r\n6. **きょう』**は木曜日です。  \r\n7. **きょう]**は木曜日です。  \r\n8. **きょう}**は木曜日です。  \r\n9. **きょう-**は木曜日です。 \r\n10. **きょう_**は木曜日です。 \r\n11. **きょう=**は木曜日です。 \r\n12. **きょう+**は木曜日です。 \r\n13. **きょう;**は木曜日です。 \r\n14. **きょう:**は木曜日です。 \r\n15. **きょう、**は木曜日です。 \r\n16. **きょう。**は木曜日です。 \r\n17. **きょう!**は木曜日です。 \r\n18. **きょう@**は木曜日です。 \r\n```\r\n\r\n2. run `python3 -m rich.markdown test.md`\r\n\r\n3. You will see that the 1st and 4th case is rendered as expected. Everything else is not. Usually Japanese is written without spaces. I suspect that some rules need to be appended for dealing with punctuation/characters within inline formatting.\r\n\r\n**Platform**\r\n- Macos Catalina\r\n- iTerm2\r\n- Rich 9.0.1\r\n","closed_by":{"login":"1dancook","id":12954427,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyOTU0NDI3","avatar_url":"https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/12954427?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/1dancook","html_url":"https://github.com/1dancook","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1dancook/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1dancook/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1dancook/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1dancook/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1dancook/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1dancook/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1dancook/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1dancook/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1dancook/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"performed_via_github_app":null}